---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Article from "../../components/Article.astro";
---

<Layout title="revelation">
  <Article
    title="revelation"
    section="mysticism"
    updated="archive draft"
  >
    <p>
      revelation is the experience of sudden disclosure—something becomes
      clear, not gradually, but all at once.
    </p>

    <p>
      it may arrive as insight, image, or felt knowing. what was hidden or
      unclear appears with a sense of certainty or inevitability.
    </p>

    <p>
      because of its force, revelation can feel authoritative. yet its meaning
      still requires time to understand.
    </p>

    <h2>disclosure</h2>

    <p>
      revelation reveals. it brings forward what was implicit or unseen,
      making it explicit in a single moment.
    </p>

    <p>
      this can reorganize perception quickly, changing how events or symbols
      are understood.
    </p>

    <h2>shock of insight</h2>

    <p>
      there is often a shock quality—an abrupt shift from not knowing to
      knowing. this intensity contributes to the sense of truth.
    </p>

    <p>
      but intensity alone is not proof. what is revealed must still be tested
      over time.
    </p>

    <h2>integration</h2>

    <p>
      revelation is a beginning, not an end. what appears must be integrated
      into life, otherwise it remains an isolated moment.
    </p>

    <p>
      integration often returns the experience to a slower pace, where meaning
      unfolds beyond the initial flash.
    </p>

    <div class="mini-links">
      <a class="link-blue" href="/mysticism">back to mysticism index</a>
      <a class="link-blue" href="/mysticism/the-unknown">continue to: the unknown</a>
      <a class="link-red" href="/mysticism/vision">vision</a>
    </div>
  </Article>
</Layout>
